Steghide
Steganography tool for hiding data in images

Forensics
Description
Steghide is a steganography tool that can hide data within JPEG, BMP, WAV, and AU files. It can also extract hidden data from these files.

Installation / Check
Check if installed:

which steghide
Install command:

sudo apt install steghide
Basic Syntax
steghide <embed|extract> -sf <file>
Common Commands
Command	What it does	When to use	Risk
steghide embed -cf cover.jpg -ef secret.txt

Hide data in image	Embed secret file in image	
steghide extract -sf stego.jpg

Extract hidden data	Reveal hidden content	
steghide info image.jpg

Get info about file	Check if image contains hidden data	
steghide embed -cf cover.jpg -ef secret.txt -p password

Embed with password	Password-protect hidden data	
Step-by-Step Guide
1
For hiding: prepare cover file and secret
2
Run embed command with password
3
For extracting: run extract on suspected file
4
Enter password if required
5
Hidden data extracted to current directory
Understanding the Output
Shows embedding capacity, compression ratio, and success/failure. Extract shows filename of extracted data.

Important Warnings
•
Steganography is often used maliciously
•
Password-protected files need password
•
Only works with specific file types
⚠️ Use Kali Linux tools only on systems you own or have written permission to test. Unauthorized hacking is illegal and can result in criminal charges.
